a_0 = 2
a_1 = 1
2^n + (-1)^n
a_{n+2} = a_{n+1} + 2a_n
a_n = c^n
 c^{n+2} = c^{n+1} + 2 c^n \implies c^2 - c - 2 = 0 \implies (c-2)(c+1) = 0 \implies c=2,-1
 \therefore a_n = A2^n + B (-1)^n
 a_0 = A + B = 2, \; \; a_1 = 2A -B = 1 \implies A=B=1
 \therefore a_n = 2^n + (-1)^n 
